abstract: >
  xgenius is an LLM-oriented autonomous research platform for SLURM clusters.
  It enables AI agents (Claude Code) to autonomously formulate hypotheses,
  modify code, submit experiments to HPC clusters, analyze results, and iterate —
  with safety guarantees for shared infrastructure. Features include structured
  job tracking, research journals, compute budget management, and a background
  watcher daemon that triggers the agent on job completion.
